***********************
CRAWLER COMPANION (MVP)
***********************

In tabletop gaming, a dungeon "crawl" allows players to quickly jump into the action with new characters and simple
stories for a fast and dirty adventure. This application works as a rudimentary companion for a Dungeon Master running
multiple "Dungeons & Dragons" games at once (or any similar tabletop RPG). Connected to a database of users, characters,
parties, plots, and campaigns (which are all freely viewable to anyone), it allows for players (users) to create
characters and even write plots they might wish to play out, and then the DM (admin) can organize all of it by placing
characters into parties and then blending parties and plots to create campaigns. All ideas are welcome, but the DM has
the final say on what stays and what goes. Only the DM can edit or delete entities from the database.

*** As an unauthenticated user, I can view lists of all existing characters, plots, parties, and campaigns.

*** As an authenticated user, I can create new characters and plots, which are added to the existing ones.

*** As an admin, I can edit/update all user details, characters, plots, parties, and campaigns. I can also assign
    users to characters and assign characters to parties, as well as remove characters from users and parties, or delete
    any of the above from the database. Using existing parties and plots, I can create and name a new campaign--and then
    delete it once the game is over.

In short, anyone can view the database, authenticated users can contribute characters and plots, and admins can edit all
of it and organize all of it into templates for playable games.